# Trivy reviewed ignore policy (RELX-05).
#
# This file is the audited allowlist read by the ci.yml build-scan Trivy
# HIGH/CRITICAL gate (wired via `trivyignores: .trivyignore`). It holds ONLY
# residual CVEs that are UNFIXABLE-but-accepted: HIGH/CRITICAL findings that
# still remain AFTER `ignore-unfixed: true` plus the base-image digest repins
# (Dockerfile.api / Dockerfile.ui), because upstream has no available fix. It is
# never a blanket mute, and the if:always SARIF run in ci.yml keeps reporting
# ALL findings to code scanning regardless of what is listed here.
#
# HARD RULE: a FIXABLE base HIGH/CRITICAL CVE is NEVER allowlisted in this file.
# A fixable CVE MUST be cleared by a base-image repin/rebuild (Task 2 digest
# bump) or escalated. Allowlisting a fixable CVE would silently weaken the very
# gate RELX-05 exists to green honestly (15-CONTEXT.md, RELX-05 decision).
#
# Per-entry acceptance format: each residual CVE is preceded by a single review
# comment line, then the bare CVE id on the next line:
#
#   # owner: <name> | reason: <why unfixable: no upstream fix available> | link: <advisory URL> | reviewed: <YYYY-MM-DD>
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN
#
# Residual entries are Claude's-discretion / operator additions driven by the
# live Trivy findings on the Linux CI runner (the actual HIGH/CRITICAL findings
# are not visible on the Windows dev box). This file is seeded with ZERO CVE
# entries: the gate greens via `ignore-unfixed: true` plus the base-image repins,
# and any genuinely unfixable residual is added below with full attribution.
#
# Residual unfixable-but-accepted CVEs (none at seed):
